data.title: Football Australia
data.meta_description:
Football Australia | 61,953 followers on LinkedIn. The governing body of Football in Australia.  | Football Australia is the governing body of football in Australia and is a member of Fédération Internationale de Football Association (FIFA), the international governing body for football.

Football Australia is a member-based organisation where membership is loosely based on Australia’s federated system of government and is comprised New South Wales, Northern New South Wales, Victoria, Queensland, Western Australia, South Australia, Australian Capital Territory, Tasmania and Northern Territory.

The Subway #Joeys have touched down in Honiara and greeted with a traditional welcome ceremony ahead of their #PacificAusSports Football Tour 🙌 🇸🇧 v 🇦🇺 - 15.8.24, 5pm AEST 🇸🇧 v 🇦🇺 - 18.8.24, 6pm AEST 🇻🇺 v 🇦🇺 - 21.8.24, 2pm AEST

Football Australia has confirmed the match schedule for the #AustraliaCup 2024 Round of 16, with several exciting clashes across three Match Days. 📰 Details: https://lnkd.in/gJDVriCM

Squad for the #U20WWC: Announced ✅ Talk about a picturesque spot for a squad announcement, our CommBank Young Matildas squad for the FIFA U-20 Women’s World Cup Colombia 2024™ was announced today at the Capybara Enclosure at Taronga Zoo! 📸 #GoAustralia

The Subway #Socceroos' new Assistant 🤝 Graham Arnold has appointed Luke Wilkshire to his coaching staff on a permanent basis ahead of our FIFA World Cup 2026™ - Canada, Mexico and the United States Round 3 qualifiers in September. 📰 Read more: https://bit.ly/4dwUGNO

Congratulations to Jarred Gillett who will referee the 2024 FA Community Shield between Manchester City and Manchester United on Sunday (AEST). 👏 Originally named fourth official, the Australian will now take charge following a minor injury sustained by John Brooks.

Sporting Schools funding applications for Term 4 are now open. 😄🙌 Apply today for Football Programs. 📝 Learn how to apply at: https://lnkd.in/gmJRN8hf

The countdown is on! 🙌⏳ In just 💯 days, the CommBank ParaMatildas will take to the pitch in Salou, Spain, for their first match in the highly anticipated IFCPF World Cup 2024, set to be held between 11 - 20 November.
